PHILOSOPHICAL HERITAGE & KNOWLEDGE SYSTEMS ATTRIBUTION

The coaching and mentoring frameworks referenced in this project are drawing inspiration from and aligned with the rich Indian philosophical heritage and traditional knowledge systems.

The following modern frameworks are adapted under fair use for educational and coaching purposes:
- VIA Character Strengths (inspired by Peterson & Seligman, 2004)
- PERMA model (Seligman, 2011)
- Adaptive Leadership framework (Heifetz & Linsky)
- Immunity to Change (Kegan & Lahey)
- Positive Intelligence / Saboteur framework (Chamine)
- Getting Things Done principles (David Allen)

This project does not claim ownership of any of these modern frameworks. Users seeking to use these frameworks in commercial coaching practices should consult the original sources for licensing requirements.

---

PSYCHOMETRIC ASSESSMENTS DISCLAIMER

The psychometric assessments in `intake/apps/` are designed for coaching
self-reflection purposes only. They are not clinically validated instruments
and should not be used for clinical assessment, hiring decisions, or any
purpose requiring validated psychometric tools. For clinical or research
applications, use validated instruments from qualified publishers.
